text:
Everyone who participated in Hacktoberfest and contributed to the <#CBBAW6Z3R|community-browser-extension>, thank you, your efforts helped other HubSpot developers all around the world.  Many of the updates that were made this month are in the beta, we will roll those updates out to the stable build soon!

Hacktoberfest is over and they’re starting to send out the swag.

While there won’t be swag in it for you (sorry the extension does not make money in any way, so I can’t give it out) - there is still a list of tasks we could use help with, as we work toward making HubSpot even better for developers.

<https://hacktoberfest.digitalocean.com/>
Easy fix..charge $0.01 per cache bust. Worth it? Definitely.

well, we’d be at $142.41(before processing fees) if we did charge 1cent per cachebust. garuntee though a lot of people wouldn’t use the the feature if they had to pay or fill out a checkout form to use it.
